{# Caddy v2 config template — Webtunnel + Let's Encrypt (Epic 488 follow-up,
   anti-censorship strategy P1 #3).

   Threat model: а VAS-class DPI active-probes veil's `:443` listener
   by issuing а plain HTTP request and inspecting the response.  An
   veil-only `webtunnel-wss://0.0.0.0:443` listener responds к non-
   secret-path requests by serving а minimal decoy from
   `webtunnel_decoy_dir`, but using а self-signed cert — the cert chain
   itself is а red flag и the decoy is one-page-thin.

   Solution: Caddy on `:443` с Let's Encrypt auto-cert serves the public
   decoy site for ANY path не matching the secret token, и reverse-
   proxies the WebSocket upgrade at `{{ webtunnel_secret_path }}` к
   veil's loopback webtunnel listener.  The combination passes:

   * **Cert authority validation** (#15 FakeTLS): real Let's Encrypt cert,
     valid for the configured hostname.  CT-log searchable.
   * **Active HTTP probe** (#15 / #20): hits Caddy's decoy site, sees
     а multi-page static site indistinguishable от any other small
     PHP-less Caddy deploy.
   * **WebSocket upgrade fingerprint**: Caddy's reverse_proxy carries
     the upgrade transparently; DPI sees а WSS connection that looks
     ordinary.

   Variables (set by `deploy-webtunnel-autotls.yml`):
     * `veil_host` — public DNS hostname (used as TLS server_name + Let's Encrypt domain)
     * `veil_email` — ACME contact email
     * `webtunnel_secret_path` — `/_t/<random32>` path that proxies к veil
     * `webtunnel_internal_port` — port on 127.0.0.1 где veil's webtunnel listens
     * `webtunnel_decoy_root` — filesystem path served as the public decoy site
-#}
# Caddy v2 config — managed by ansible/deploy-webtunnel-autotls.yml.
# Manual edits will be overwritten on re-deploy.

{
    email {{ veil_email }}
    # Auto HTTPS on 443; HTTP on 80 is automatically redirected к HTTPS.
    auto_https on
    # Standard ACME directory.  Operators in regions where the default
    # endpoint is blocked can switch к ZeroSSL via:
    #   acme_ca https://acme.zerossl.com/v2/DV90
}

{{ veil_host }} {
    # ── Webtunnel reverse-proxy ───────────────────────────────────────
    # The secret path is а 32-char random token randomly chosen at
    # deploy time.  Caddy proxies any request к this path к veil's
    # loopback listener on `webtunnel_internal_port`.  Anything else
    # (including а bare GET /) falls through к the static decoy site.
    @veil path {{ webtunnel_secret_path }}*
    handle @veil {
        reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:{{ webtunnel_internal_port }} {
            # WSS upgrade requires HTTP/1.1; advertise as such even
            # though Caddy will speak HTTP/2 к the client by default.
            transport http {
                versions 1.1
            }
            # Forward the standard upgrade-headers so veil's
            # webtunnel handler sees the WS handshake unchanged.
            header_up Connection {>Connection}
            header_up Upgrade {>Upgrade}
            header_up Sec-WebSocket-Key {>Sec-WebSocket-Key}
            header_up Sec-WebSocket-Version {>Sec-WebSocket-Version}
            header_up Sec-WebSocket-Protocol {>Sec-WebSocket-Protocol}
            header_up Sec-WebSocket-Extensions {>Sec-WebSocket-Extensions}
            # X-Real-IP for veil's scanner-shield IP-banning logic.
            header_up X-Real-IP {remote_host}
            header_up X-Forwarded-For {remote_host}
        }
    }

    # ── Static decoy site ─────────────────────────────────────────────
    # Server every other path from `webtunnel_decoy_root`.  Multi-page
    # site (index.html + about.html + sitemap.xml + robots.txt) что
    # passes "looks like а real small website" active-probe heuristics.
    handle {
        root * {{ webtunnel_decoy_root }}
        file_server {
            hide .git .gitignore .DS_Store
        }
        # Standard security headers — also makes the site look mundane.
        header {
            X-Content-Type-Options "nosniff"
            Referrer-Policy "strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
            Strict-Transport-Security "max-age=31536000"
            Cache-Control "public, max-age=3600"
            # Remove the default Caddy banner — operator anonymity.
            -Server
        }
    }

    # ── Operational logging ───────────────────────────────────────────
    log {
        output file /var/log/caddy/access.log {
            roll_size 10mb
            roll_keep 5
            roll_keep_for 720h
        }
        # Don't log request bodies — those may include the webtunnel
        # WS payload which is encrypted but identifying length-wise.
        format json
        level WARN
    }
}
